igion in Serbia]]\n[[Category:Religion in Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Religion in Slovenia]]\n[[Category:Religion in the Czech Republic]]\n", "name_user": "DayakSibiriak", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDead Water:cr", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slavic_Native_Faith"}
{"title_page": "Banj\u00eb Hydro Power Plant", "text_new": "{{Infobox dam\n| name = Banj\u00eb Hydro Power Plant\n| name_official = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_caption = \n| image_alt = \n| location_map = Albania\n| location_map_size = \n| location_map_caption = \n| coordinates = {{coord|40.964|20.068|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n| country = [[Albania]]\n| location = [[Klos, Elbasan|Banj\u00eb]]\n| construction_began = \n| opening = \n| demolished = \n| cost = \n| owner = [[Statkraft|Devoll Hydropower]]\n| dam_type = \n| dam_height = 80\n| dam_height_thalweg = \n| dam_height_foundation = \n| dam_length = \n| dam_width_crest = \n| dam_width_base = \n| dam_volume = \n| dam_elevation_crest = 175\n| dam_crosses = [[Devoll (river)|Devoll]]\n| spillway_count = \n| spillway_type = \n| spillway_capacity = \n| res_name = \n| res_capacity_total = 400 million m<sup>3</sup>\n| res_capacity_active = \n| res_capacity_inactive = \n| res_catchment = \n| res_surface = 14 km<sup>2</sup>\n| res_elevation = \n| res_max_depth = \n| res_max_length = \n| res_max_width = \n| res_tidal_range = \n| plant_operator = \n| plant_commission = September 2016\n| plant_decommission = \n| plant_type = \n| plant_turbines = \n| plant_capacity = 70&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]]\n| plant_annual_gen = \n| website = \n| extra = \n}}\n'''Banj\u00eb Hydro Power Plant''' is a large [[hydroelectricity]] plant on the river [[Devoll (river)|Devoll]] situated near the village [[Klos, Elbasan|Banj\u00eb]], [[Albania]]. It was built by Devoll Hydropower, an Albanian company owned by Norwegian power company [[Statkraft]]. The project consists of a large power plant with a nominal capacity of 70 [[Megawatt|MW]] and an average annual production of 242 GWh.<ref>[http://www.devollhydropower.al/new/?page_id=7436 Devoll Hydropower]</ref> The dam is 900 m long, 370 m wide and 80 m high.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Devoll Hydropower  {{!}} F.A.Q|url = http://www.devollhydropower.al/new/?page_id=7754|website = www.devollhydropower.al|accessdate = 2015-11-03}}</ref> The reservoir was planned to have a surface area of 14&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>, and a storage capacity of about 400 million m<sup>3</sup>. It was completed in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.statkraft.com/energy-sources/Power-plants/albania/banja/|title=Banja {{!}} Statkraft|website=www.statkraft.com|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{stack|{{Portal|Water|Renewable energy}}}}\n{{Energy in Albania}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Banje Hydro Power Plant}}\n[[Category:Hydroelectric power stations in Albania]]\n[[Category:C\u00ebrrik]]\n\n\n{{Albania-struct-stub}}\n{{Hydroelectric-power-plant-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox dam\n| name = Banj\u00eb Hydro Power Plant\n| name_official = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_caption = \n| image_alt = \n| location_map = Albania\n| location_map_size = \n| location_map_caption = \n| coordinates = {{coord|40.964|20.068|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n| country = [[Albania]]\n| location = [[Klos, Elbasan|Banj\u00eb]]\n| construction_began = \n| opening = \n| demolished = \n| cost = \n| owner = [[Statkraft|Devoll Hydropower]]\n| dam_type = \n| dam_height = 80\n| dam_height_thalweg = \n| dam_height_foundation = \n| dam_length = \n| dam_width_crest = \n| dam_width_base = \n| dam_volume = \n| dam_elevation_crest = 175\n| dam_crosses = [[Devoll (river)|Devoll]]\n| spillway_count = \n| spillway_type = \n| spillway_capacity = \n| res_name = \n| res_capacity_total = 400 million m<sup>3</sup>\n| res_capacity_active = \n| res_capacity_inactive = \n| res_catchment = \n| res_surface = 14 km<sup>2</sup>\n| res_elevation = \n| res_max_depth = \n| res_max_length = \n| res_max_width = \n| res_tidal_range = \n| plant_operator = \n| plant_commission = September 2016\n| plant_decommission = \n| plant_type = \n| plant_turbines = \n| plant_capacity = 70&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]]\n| plant_annual_gen = \n| website = \n| extra = \n}}\n'''Banj\u00eb Hydro Power Plant''' is a large [[hydroelectricity]] plant on the river [[Devoll (river)|Devoll]] situated near the village [[Klos, Elbasan|Banj\u00eb]], [[Albania]]. It is built by Devoll Hydropower, an Albanian company owned by Norwegian power company [[Statkraft]]. The project consists of a large power plant with a nominal capacity of 70 [[Megawatt|MW]] and an average annual production of 242 GWh.<ref>[http://www.devollhydropower.al/new/?page_id=7436 Devoll Hydropower]</ref> The dam is 900 m long, 370 m wide and 80 m high.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Devoll Hydropower  {{!}} F.A.Q|url = http://www.devollhydropower.al/new/?page_id=7754|website = www.devollhydropower.al|accessdate = 2015-11-03}}</ref> The reservoir was planned to have a surface area of 14&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>, and a storage capacity of about 400 million m<sup>3</sup>. It was completed in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.statkraft.com/energy-sources/Power-plants/albania/banja/|title=Banja {{!}} Statkraft|website=www.statkraft.com|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{stack|{{Portal|Water|Renewable energy}}}}\n{{Energy in Albania}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Banje Hydro Power Plant}}\n[[Category:Hydroelectric power stations in Albania]]\n[[Category:Proposed hydroelectric power stations]]\n[[Category:C\u00ebrrik]]\n\n\n{{Albania-struct-stub}}\n{{Hydroelectric-power-plant-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Macquaria", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removed from category \"Proposed hydroelectric power stations\" since this project is now complete.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banj%C3%AB_Hydro_Power_Plant"}
{"title_page": "Timeline of the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia", "text_new": "{{short description|Sequence of major events in ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Indonesia}}\n{{Current event|date=April 2020}}\nThis article documents the timeline of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia|coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia]].\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Indonesia medical cases chart}}\n\n==February==\n\n===2 February===\n* The Indonesian government evacuated 243 Indonesian nationals from [[Wuhan]], [[China]]. The repatriated Indonesians were placed under quarantine in the [[Natuna Regency|Natuna Islands]] but were not tested as they were asymptomatic.<ref name=\"Feb2020\">{{cite web \n|title=Indonesian Government Successfully Repatriated 243 People From Wuhan China {{!}} Portal Kementerian Luar Negeri Republik Indonesia \n|url=https://kemlu.go.id/portal/en/read/1011/berita/indonesian-government-successfully-repatriated-243-people-from-wuhan-china \n|website=kemlu.go.id \n|publisher=MINISTRY OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS OF THE REPUBLIC OF INDONESIA \n|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2020/03/indonesia-finally-reports-two-coronavirus-cases-scientists-worry-it-has-many-more|first=Dyna|last= Rochmyaningsih|date=3 March 2020|title=Indonesia finally reports two coronavirus cases. Scientists worry it has many more|work=American Association for the Advancement of Science|accessdate=3 March 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n===24 February===\n* 9 Indonesians on board the ''[[Diamond Princess (ship)|Diamond Princess]]'' tested positive for the virus and were moved to treatment facilities in [[Japan]]. The Indonesian government repatriated and then quarantined the remaining 68 crew members, along with the 188 from the ''[[World Dream]]'', onto the uninhabited Sebaru Kecil Island in the [[Thousand Islands (Indonesia)|Thousand Islands]] off the coast of [[Jakarta]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/24/number-of-indonesians-with-coronavirus-on-diamond-princess-rises-to-nine.html\n|title=Number of Indonesians with coronavirus on Diamond Princess rises to nine\n|author1=Marchio Irfan Gorbiano\n|author2=Budi Sutrisno \n|work=The Jakarta Post\n|date=2020-02-24\n|accessdate=2020-03-05\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200224144659-4-140074/wni-kena-corona-di-kapal-diamond-princess-kini-jadi-9-orang \n|title=WNI Kena Corona di Kapal Diamond Princess Kini Jadi 9 orang\n|trans-title=Indonesian Citizens Affected by Corona on the Diamond Princess Ship are now 9 people\n|work=CNBC Indonesia\n|date=24 February 2020\n|accessdate=24 February 2020\n|language=id\n|url-status=live\n}}</ref>\n\n==March==\n\n[[File:CoViD-19 ID.svg|thumb|upright=2|left|Number of cases (blue) and number of deaths (red) on a [[logarithmic scale]].]]\n\n===2 March===\n* President [[Joko Widodo]] confirmed the first two cases of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] in the country in a televised statement.<ref name=\"straitstimes\">{{cite news |author=Linda Yulisman |title=Mother and daughter test positive for coronavirus in Indonesia, first confirmed cases in the country |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/indonesia-confirms-two-coronavirus-cases-president |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=The Straits Times |issue=Asia |date=2 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> According to the Minister of Health [[Terawan Agus Putranto]], the patients contracted the virus from an infected Japanese person in [[Depok]] who later tested positive in [[Malaysia]].<ref name=\"theguardian-ratcliffe\" /> Both Indonesian patients were subsequently hospitalized at Sulianti Saroso Infection Center Hospital, [[North Jakarta]].\n\n===6 March===\n* As of 6 March, Indonesia had only tested 450 individuals out of its 270 million population.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://infeksiemerging.kemkes.go.id/uncategorized/situasi-terkini-perkembangan-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-6-maret-2020\n|title=Situasi Terkini Perkembangan Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) 6 Maret 2020\n|work=Info Infeksi Emerging Kementerian Kesehatan RI\n|language=id\n|date=2020-03-06\n|accessdate=2020-03-06\n}}</ref>\n\n===7 March===\n* One of the crew evacuated from the ''Diamond Princess'' was suspected of contracting the disease and was subsequently transferred to an isolation unit at Persahabatan Central General Hospital, [[East Jakarta]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/another-diamond-princess-crew-member-from-indonesia-suspected-of-contracting-coronavirus|title=Another Diamond Princess Crew Member From Indonesia Suspected of Contracting Coronavirus|website=Jakarta Globe|date=2020-03-06|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n===8 March===\n* A 50-year-old woman from Jakarta tested positive in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]. She began showing symptoms two days after flying to [[Perth]] from Jakarta on 27 February and saw a GP four days after arriving in Melbourne on 2 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/victoria/indonesian-woman-becomes-12th-victorian-covid-19-case-20200308-p54809.html|title=Indonesian woman becomes 12th Victorian COVID-19 case|work=The Age|language=en|date=2020-03-08|accessdate=2020-03-08|first=Tate|last=Papworth}}</ref>\n* The government of Indonesia announced two more confirmed cases. One patient was infected through close contact with case #1, the other patient being a crew member of the Diamond Princess.<ref name=\"8Mar20\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200308162030-20-481536/pasien-positif-virus-corona-bertambah-jadi-6-orang|title=Pasien Positif Corona Bertambah Jadi 6 Orang|work=CNN Indonesia|language=id|date=2020-03-08|accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n===9 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed 13 new cases of COVID-19 infection, 2 of them being foreigners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4931659/melonjak-pasien-positif-corona-di-wilayah-ri-jadi-19-orang|title=Melonjak! Pasien Positif Corona di Wilayah RI Jadi 19 Orang|author=Andhika Prasetia |website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-09|date=2020-03-09}}</ref> The Indonesian government decided not to disclose the detection location of the patient and the treatment facility used.{{citation  needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n===10 March===\n* 2 patients who were previously confirmed to be positive were subsequently reported as negative, substantiating an explanation made by an Indonesian government representative. The two patients were to be discharged, should further test confirm their negative status.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/internasional/d-4932718/kabar-baik-pasien-kasus-06-dan-14-sudah-negatif-corona|title=Kabar Baik! Pasien Kasus 06 dan 14 Sudah Negatif Corona|author=Kadek Melda Luxiana|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-10|date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n*Indonesia confirmed 8 new cases of COVID-19 infection, 2 of them foreigners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4933267/jadi-27-orang-ini-detail-8-pasien-baru-virus-corona|title=Jadi 27 Orang, Ini Detail 8 Pasien Baru Virus Corona|author=Kadek Melda Luxiana|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-10|date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n*A suspected COVID-19 patient fleed from Persahabatan Central General Hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4937896/pasien-positif-corona-kabur-dari-rs-persahabatan-dijemput-keluarga|title=Pasien Positif Corona Kabur dari RS Persahabatan, Dijemput Keluarga|last=Luqman|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4937970/alasan-pasien-positif-corona-kabur-tak-mau-sekamar-isolasi-berdua|title=Alasan Pasien Positif Corona Kabur: Tak Mau Sekamar Isolasi Berdua|last=Arunata|first=Luqman Nurhadi|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref> She was later confirmed as positive of the virus and has returned to the hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4938404/pasien-corona-yang-sempat-kabur-dipastikan-sudah-kembali-ke-rs-persahabatan|title=Pasien Corona yang Sempat Kabur Dipastikan Sudah Kembali ke RS Persahabatan|last=Luxiana|first=Kadek Melda|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===11 March===\n* Case #25 died due to complications of the disease.<ref name=death>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/11/13061741/breaking-news-satu-pasien-covid-19-di-indonesia-meninggal-dunia|title=BREAKING NEWS: Satu Pasien Covid-19 di Indonesia Meninggal Dunia|author=Ihsanuddin|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-11|date=2020-03-11}}</ref> The victim was a British national and died in [[Bali]]'s hospital.<ref name=death2/>\n*Indonesia confirmed 7 new cases of COVID-19 infection, all of them imported cases.<ref name=:34>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4934881/pasien-positif-virus-corona-jadi-34-orang-2-sembuh-1-meninggal|title=Pasien Positif Virus Corona Jadi 34 Orang: 2 Sembuh, 1 Meninggal|author=Kanavino Ahmad Rizqo |website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref>\n\n===12 March===\n* 5 cases recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4936834/data-terbaru-corona-terkait-indonesia-12-maret-2020-pukul-2100-wib/3|title=Data Terbaru Corona Terkait Indonesia, 12 Maret 2020 Pukul 21.00 WIB|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|date=2020-03-12|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n*[[:id:Daftar Menteri Ketenagakerjaan Indonesia|Indonesian Labour Minister]] [[:id:Ida Fauziyah|Ida Fauziah]] mandated that all Indonesian companies provide their employees with coronavirus prevention equipment, such as face masks and hand sanitizer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4935342/perusahaan-wajib-sediakan-masker-demi-cegah-corona|title=Perusahaan Wajib Sediakan Masker Demi Cegah Corona|last=Indraini|first=Anisa|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===13 March===\n* 3 coronavirus-linked deaths were reported, 1 case in [[Surakarta|Solo]], [[Central Java]].<ref name=death3>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kompas.com/tren/read/2020/03/13/120826665/satu-pasien-isolasi-yang-meninggal-di-rsud-moewardi-solo-positif-corona|title=Satu Pasien Isolasi yang Meninggal di RSUD Moewardi Solo Positif Corona|author=Labib Zamani|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-13|date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4937577/ini-detail-pasien-virus-corona-yang-meninggal-di-solo|title=Ini Detail Pasien Virus Corona yang Meninggal di Solo|author=Firdaus Anwar|website=Detik.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-13|date=2020-03-13}}</ref> The other two were undisclosed.<ref name=\"Andhika Prasetia\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4938023/kasus-positif-corona-di-ri-jadi-69|title=Kasus Positif Corona di RI Jadi 69|author=Andhika Prasetia|website=Detik.com|date=2020-03-13|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4938060/total-4-pasien-positif-corona-meninggal-dunia|title=Total 4 Pasien Positif Corona Meninggal Dunia|author=Zunita Putri|website=Detik.com|date=2020-03-13|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n* Indonesia confirmed 35 new cases of COVID-19 infection, totalling 69 cases.<ref name=\"Andhika Prasetia\"/>\n* The first affected medical worker died on 13 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/14/18404141/yurianto-ada-petugas-medis-positif-corona-yang-meninggal-dunia|title=Yurianto: Ada Petugas Medis Positif Corona yang Meninggal Dunia|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14|date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===14 March===\n* The Indonesian government confirmed 27 new cases of COVID-19, a total of 96 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4939115/ada-27-kasus-baru-pasien-positif-corona-di-indonesia-jadi-96-orang|title=Ada 27 Kasus Baru, Pasien Positif Corona di Indonesia Jadi 96 Orang|last=Rahayu|first=Lisye Sri|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> \n* This date also marks the first time that the government announced the locations with confirmed coronavirus cases. Locations with confirmed coronavirus cases included every district in [[Jakarta]], [[Tangerang]] in [[Banten]], [[Bandung]] in [[West Java]], [[Surakarta|Solo]] in [[Central Java]], [[Yogyakarta]] in [[Special Region of Yogyakarta]], [[Pontianak, West Kalimantan|Pontianak]] in [[West Kalimantan]], [[Manado]] in [[North Sulawesi]] and [[Bali]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Daerah yang Terdapat Positif Corona: dari Bandung ke Manado|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200314164544-20-483432/daerah-yang-terdapat-positif-corona-dari-bandung-ke-manado|publisher=CNN Indonesia|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n* 3 further patients recovered, for a total of 8 recovered patients.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/14/16452961/update-tambah-3-total-8-orang-sembuh-dari-corona-di-indonesia|title=UPDATE: Tambah 3, Total 8 Orang Sembuh dari Corona di Indonesia|author=Ihsanuddin |website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14|date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n* 1 patient died, bringing the total to 5 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939143/pasien-meninggal-akibat-corona-di-ri-bertambah-jadi-5|title=Pasien Meninggal Akibat Corona di RI Bertambah Jadi 5|author=Rahel Narda Chatrine|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14|date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n* [[Ministry of Transportation (Indonesia)|Indonesian Minister of Transportation]], [[Budi Karya Sumadi]] tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939392/menhub-budi-karya-pasien-positif-corona-kasus-76|title=Menhub Budi Karya Pasien Positif Corona Kasus 76|author=Andhika Prasetia|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Menhub Budi Karya Sumadi positif COVID-19 |url=https://www.antaranews.com/berita/1356658/menhub-budi-karya-sumadi-positif-covid-19|language=id |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=Antara News |date=14 March 2020}}</ref> A few days prior, on 10 March, Budi Karya was diagnosed with typhoid fever after travelling to [[Wakatobi Regency|Wakatobi]], [[Toraja]], [[Luwuk]], [[Makassar]], [[Parepare]], [[Kertajati International Airport|Kertajati]], and [[Indramayu]]. His travel history included travel to [[Kertajati International Airport]] on 1 March that had acted as an evacuation centre for the repatriated crew of the Diamond Princess. One of the crew of Diamond Princess tested positive for COVID-19 on 8 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4933161/menhub-jatuh-sakit-jubir-kena-gejala-tifus|title=Menhub Jatuh Sakit, Jubir: Kena Gejala Tifus|last=Prasetia|first=Andhika|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> On 11 March, Budi had also met with the Dutch Minister of Infrastructure and Water Management [[Cora van Nieuwenhuizen|Cora Van Nieuwenhuize]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939440/menhub-sempat-ke-istana-bertemu-pejabat-belanda-sebelum-positif-corona|title=Menhub Sempat ke Istana-Bertemu Pejabat Belanda Sebelum Positif Corona|last=Prasetia|first=Andhika|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===15 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed 21 new cases of COVID-19 infection, 19 in [[Jakarta]] and 2 in [[Central Java]], a total of 117 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200315133445-20-483573/21-kasus-baru-pasien-positif-corona-indonesia-jadi-117-orang|title=21 Kasus Baru, Pasien Positif Corona Indonesia Jadi 117 Orang|work=CNN Indonesia|language=id|date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939844/pasien-positif-corona-bertambah-21-kasus-total-jadi-117-kasus|title=Pasien Positif Corona Bertambah 21 Kasus, Total Jadi 117 Kasus|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15|date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n*Indonesian President [[Joko Widodo]] is said to be undergoing a COVID-19 test in the evening.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939909/presiden-jokowi-jalani-tes-virus-corona-sore-ini|title=Presiden Jokowi Jalani Tes Virus Corona Sore Ini|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15|date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n===16 March===\n* Indonesian Vice-President [[Ma'ruf Amin]] and Indonesian Interior Minister [[Tito Karnavian]] have tested negative on the COVID-19 test.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/16/10390031/sudah-tes-wapres-maruf-amin-negatif-covid-19|title=Sudah Tes, Wapres Ma'ruf Amin Negatif Covid-19|author=Deti Mega Purnamasari|editor=Diamanty Meiliana|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200316140224-4-145183/usai-tes-covid-19-di-rspad-tito-istri-dipastikan-sehat|title=Usai Tes Covid-19 di RSPAD, Tito & Istri Dipastikan Sehat|last=Iqbal|first=Muhammad|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n*Indonesia confirmed 17 new cases of infection, in a total of 134 cases. 14 new cases in Jakarta, 1 new case in Central Java, 1 new case in Banten, and 1 new case in West Java.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4941340/ada-tambahan-17-pasien-corona-baru-14-di-antaranya-dari-jakarta|title=Ada Tambahan 17 Pasien Corona Baru, 14 di Antaranya dari Jakarta|last=Luxiana|first=Kadek Melda|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n*Indonesia announced that it will start to quarantine asymptomatic COVID-19 patients in their own home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4941325/kemenkes-sekarang-pasien-positif-corona-bisa-diisolasi-mandiri-di-rumah|title=Kemenkes: Sekarang Pasien Positif Corona Bisa Diisolasi Mandiri di Rumah|last=Melda|first=Kadek|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n===17 March===\n* In response to the growing number of COVID-19 cases in Indonesia, the [[Indonesian National Board for Disaster Management]] declared an emergency period for 91 days, effective until 29 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pemerintah Tetapkan Masa Darurat Bencana Corona hingga 29 Mei 2020|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942327/pemerintah-tetapkan-masa-darurat-bencana-corona-hingga-29-mei-2020?tag_from=news_mostpop|publisher=Detik|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n* The Indonesian government announced 38 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total number of infections to 172.<ref>{{cite web|title=Data Terbaru Virus Corona: Total Kasus Positif Melonjak Jadi 172|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942786/data-terbaru-virus-corona-total-kasus-positif-melonjak-jadi-172|publisher=Detik|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n*1 case recovered, adding to a total of 9 cases recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4942803/virus-corona-indonesia-jadi-172-kasus-9-sembuh-5-meninggal|title=Virus Corona Indonesia Jadi 172 Kasus, 9 Sembuh 5 Meninggal|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n*2 patients died (1 in Semarang and another one still unknown), in a total of 7 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200317210849-20-484354/pasien-meninggal-akibat-corona-bertambah-jadi-7-orang|title=Pasien Meninggal Akibat Corona Bertambah Jadi 7 Orang|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n*There are mistakes in the counting of the deaths.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://tirto.id/update-corona-di-ri-172-positif-7-meninggal-wni-diminta-pulang-eFLZ | title=Update Corona di RI: 172 Positif, 7 Meninggal & WNI Diminta Pulang}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4943106/gubernur-banten-umumkan-1-warga-positif-corona-meninggal-kemenkes-tak-tahu|title=Gubernur Banten Umumkan 1 Warga Positif Corona Meninggal, Kemenkes Tak Tahu|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> The minister of health reported that the total number of the death is still 5, the same as that on 14 March<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942786/data-terbaru-virus-corona-total-kasus-positif-melonjak-jadi-172?tag_from=wp_cb_mostPopular_list&_ga=2.238927360.105839233.1584339272-1415494084.1580723020|title=Data Terbaru Virus Corona: Total Kasus Positif Melonjak Jadi 172|last=detikcom|first=tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> while two new deaths were reported in the early morning by Governor of Central Java<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-tengah/d-4942759/1-pasien-positif-corona-meninggal-di-rs-kariadi-semarang-hari-ini|title=1 Pasien Positif Corona Meninggal di RS Kariadi Semarang Hari Ini|last=Purbaya|first=Angling Adhitya|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> and Governor of Banten.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942389/gubernur-banten-1-pasien-positif-corona-di-pondok-aren-meninggal|title=Gubernur Banten: 1 Pasien Positif Corona di Pondok Aren Meninggal|last=Komara|first=Indra|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> The total number of deaths should be 7.\n\n===18 March===\n*Indonesia confirmed 55 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total up to 227 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944276/update-terbaru-virus-corona-di-indonesia-total-kasus-positif-jadi-227-orang|title=Update Terbaru Virus Corona di Indonesia: Total Kasus Positif Jadi 227 Orang|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n*12 patients died, the number of deaths has now increased to 19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944358/pernyataan-lengkap-pemerintah-soal-227-kasus-positif-corona-dan-19-meninggal|title=Pernyataan Lengkap Pemerintah soal 227 Kasus Positif Corona dan 19 Meninggal|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> The 19 fatalities mean that Indonesia has now recorded the highest death toll among Southeast Asian countries hit by the coronavirus to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/18/covid-19-indonesia-records-highest-death-toll-in-southeast-asia-at-19.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesia records highest death toll in Southeast Asia at 19|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Indonesia's case fatality rate has reached 8.37% which is double the world case fatality rate (4.07%).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944800/tingkat-kematian-pasien-corona-di-ri-837-bagaimana-negara-lain|title=Tingkat Kematian Pasien Corona di RI 8,37%, Bagaimana Negara Lain?|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n*7 Indonesians in [[India]] tested positive for COVID-19 were a part of a 10-member team who travelled to [[Karimnagar]] for a religious tour.<ref name=\"TH1\">{{cite news |last1=Geetanath |first1=K. Shiva Shankar & V. |title=Coronavirus {{!}} Telangana reports 8 new COVID-19 cases |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/telangana-reports-8-new-covid-19-cases/article31102733.ece?homepage=true |newspaper=The Hindu |language=en-IN |date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*After 2 positive cases, Governor of West Kalimantan [[Sutarmidji]] declares an \"extraordinary event\" until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944658/ada-2-kasus-positif-gubernur-tetapkan-kalbar-klb-corona|title=Ada 2 Kasus Positif, Gubernur Tetapkan Kalbar KLB Corona|last=Kholid|first=Idham|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n===19 March===\n* Joko Widodo announces 7 critical points (mass rapid tests, incentive for medical personnel, involve religious people, stop exporting medical equipment, stop holiday, incentive for small and medium enterprises, increase food stocks) to accelerate the elimination of COVID-19 outbreak in Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4945259/ini-arahan-lengkap-terbaru-jokowi-untuk-tangani-virus-corona|title=Ini Arahan Lengkap Terbaru Jokowi untuk Tangani Virus Corona|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=LIVE : Rapat Terbatas Laporan Tim Gugus Tugas COVID-19, Istana Merdeka, 19 Maret 2020|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NnpUlfKq74U|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/19/15282081/7-arahan-terbaru-jokowi-untuk-penanganan-covid-19|title=7 Arahan Terbaru Jokowi untuk Penanganan Covid-19 Halaman all|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*Indonesia announced 82 new cases, bringing the total to 309 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/19/15531171/update-total-pasien-covid-19-di-indonesia-kini-309-kasus|title=UPDATE: Total Pasien Covid-19 di Indonesia Kini 309 Kasus|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4945783/kasus-wni-positif-corona-melonjak-dari-227-jadi-309|title=Kasus WNI Positif Corona Melonjak dari 227 Jadi 309|last=Sidik|first=Farih Maulana|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> However, it is revised to 308 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200319182124-4-146252/pemerintah-meralat-kasus-positif-corona-di-ri-jadi-308-kasus|title=Pemerintah Meralat: Kasus Positif Corona di RI Jadi 308 Kasus|last=dob|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*4 more patients in DKI Jakarta announced cured from COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/19/16104301/update-15-orang-dinyatakan-sembuh-dari-covid-19|title=UPDATE: 15 Orang Dinyatakan Sembuh dari Covid-19|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*The import of Rapid Test Tools (15 minutes - 3 hours) by [[:id:Rajawali Nusantara Indonesia|Rajawali Nusantara Indonesia]] from China has been approved by [[Ministry of Health (Indonesia)|Ministry of Health]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4945868/alat-cek-virus-corona-15-menit-mulai-masuk-ke-ri-hari-ini|title=Alat Cek Virus Corona 15 Menit Mulai Masuk ke RI Hari Ini|last=Afriyadi|first=Achmad Dwi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4944943/ri-mau-beli-alat-tes-corona-secepat-kilat-buatan-china|title=RI Mau Beli Alat Tes Corona 'Secepat Kilat' Buatan China|last=Afriyadi|first=Achmad Dwi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n* President Joko Widodo and wife, [[Iriana]], tested negative on the COVID-19 test.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4945942/jokowi-saya-dan-ibu-iriana-alhamdulillah-negatif-corona|title=Jokowi: Saya dan Ibu Iriana Alhamdulillah Negatif Corona|last=Erwanti|first=Marlinda Oktavia|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n* Indonesian Chief of Police [[Idham Azis]] publishes notice for all policeman to disperse crowds anywhere at anytime, including restaurants, matrimony and religious services, and to deny permits for large events.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Putra |first1=Nanda Permana |title=Isi Maklumat Kapolri Terkait Corona yang Buat Kapolsek Kembangan Dicopot |url=https://www.liputan6.com/news/read/4217314/isi-maklumat-kapolri-terkait-corona-yang-buat-kapolsek-kembangan-dicopot |accessdate=3 April 2020 |publisher=Liputan6.com |date=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n* The government cancelled a [[Tablighi Jamaat]] event in the [[Gowa Regency]] in [[Sulawesi]]. Thousands had already gathered despite a call for it to be cancelled earlier. A similar gathering in Kuala Lumpur in late February had caused a large outbreak of Covid-19 cases in Malaysia including 3 Indonesians.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2020/03/19/indonesia-cancels-international-muslim-gathering-as-virus-risk-mounts |title= Indonesia cancels international Muslim gathering as virus risk mounts |date= 19 March 2020|work=The Star}}</ref>\n\n===20 March===\n* Indonesia announced 60 new cases, bringing the total to 369 cases. Indonesia also announced 17 recovered and 32 deaths, an increase of 7 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947188/data-terbaru-369-positif-corona-meningkat-60-kasus|title=Data Terbaru: 369 Positif Corona, Meningkat 60 Kasus|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*Indonesia Minister of State-Owned Enterprises [[Erick Thohir]] that Indonesia has enough drugs for 60,000 COVID-19 patients, and by the end of March could supply up to 4.7 million face masks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4947190/erick-thohir-obat-pasien-corona-bisa-untuk-60-ribu-orang|title=Erick Thohir: Obat Pasien Corona Bisa untuk 60 Ribu Orang|last=Afriyadi|first=Achmad Dwi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*President Joko Widodo instructed his officials to shift budgetary priorities. Less prioritized budgets from the state budget (APBN) and regional budget (APBD) are to be reallocated to fund government efforts in combating the coronavirus pandemic, increasing the safety net for Indonesians, and to incentivize small and medium businesses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibizmedia.com/2020/03/20/hadapi-tantangan-pandemi-covid-19-ini-tiga-prioritas-kerja-pemerintah/|title=Hadapi Tantangan Pandemi Covid-19, Ini Tiga Prioritas Kerja Pemerintah|last=Sinambela|first=Maruli|date=2020-03-20|website=Vibizmedia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> He also promised to begin deploying rapid coronavirus testing, prioritizing South Jakarta as the worst-hit area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947166/pemerintah-mulai-rapid-test-corona-hari-ini-jakarta-jadi-prioritas|title=Pemerintah Mulai Rapid Test Corona Hari Ini, Jakarta Jadi Prioritas|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*Anies Baswedan declares a state of emergency in Jakarta for the next 14 days (2 April).<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947518/corona-ancam-jakarta-anies-tetapkan-status-tanggap-darurat-bencana|title=Corona Ancam Jakarta, Anies Tetapkan Status Tanggap Darurat Bencana|last=Wahid|first=Ahmad Bil|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> Anies also urged businesses to suspend operations, and he urged all stakeholders to take drastic actions to prevent the spread of the disease during the state of emergency.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947558/anies-minta-perusahaan-hentikan-kegiatan-perkantoran|title=Anies Minta Perusahaan Hentikan Kegiatan Perkantoran|last=Wahid|first=Ahmad Bil|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/20/breaking-jakarta-declares-covid-19-emergency-urges-offices-to-suspend-operation-for-14-days.html|title=BREAKING: Jakarta declares COVID-19 emergency, urges offices to suspend operation for 14 days|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*After 9 positive cases of COVID-19, [[Khofifah Indar Parawansa]] declares a state of emergency for [[East Java]].<ref name=\"9Positive\">{{Cite web|url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/20/18240621/9-orang-positif-covid-19-khofifah-tetapkan-jatim-darurat-virus-corona|title=9 Orang Positif Covid-19, Khofifah Tetapkan Jatim Darurat Virus Corona|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-21|trans-title=9 Positive People Covid-19, Khofifah Determine Corona Virus Emergency East Java}}</ref>\n*Mayor of [[Bogor]], [[Bima Arya Sugiarto|Bima Arya]] has tested positive for COVID-19 after a trip to Turkey.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4946411/wali-kota-bogor-bima-arya-positif-corona|title=Wali Kota Bogor Bima Arya Positif Corona|last=Mawardi|first=Isal|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> Bima and all officials who went on the trip will comply with health protocols that include a minimum 14-day isolation at Bogor Senior Hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/20/bogor-mayor-one-other-official-test-positive-for-covid-19-after-trip-to-turkey.html|title=Bogor mayor, one other official test positive for COVID-19 after trip to Turkey|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*[[:id:Detri Warmanto|Detri Warmanto]] has tested positive for COVID-19. He is the son-in-law of the [[Ministry of Administrative and Bureaucratic Reform|Minister of Administrative and Bureaucratic Reform]], [[Tjahjo Kumolo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hot.detik.com/celeb/d-4947822/pemain-film-3-srikandi-detri-warmanto-positif-corona|title=Pemain Film '3 Srikandi', Detri Warmanto Positif Corona|last=Febrian|first=Prih Prawesti|website=detikhot|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*[[Istiqlal Mosque, Jakarta|Istiqlal mosque]] halted [[Friday prayer]] for 2 weeks after Anies Baswedan and [[Indonesian Council of Ulama]] requested to halt mass religious activities in Jakarta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liputan6.com/news/read/4206735/masjid-istiqlal-tiadakan-salat-jumat-selama-2-pekan|title=Masjid Istiqlal Tiadakan Salat Jumat Selama 2 Pekan|last=Liputan6.com|date=2020-03-20|website=liputan6.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n===21 March===\n*[[Indonesian Air Force]] is to fly its [[Lockheed C-130 Hercules|C-130 Hercules]] (A-1333) to the Chinese city of [[Shanghai]] on Saturday to pick up approximately 9 tonnes of medical equipment. The route is [[Malang]]-[[Natuna Regency|Natuna]]-Hainan-Shanghai. The equipment includes disposable masks, [[N95 mask]]s, protective clothing, goggles, gloves, shoe covers, infrared thermometers, and surgical caps.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4948247/tni-kerahkan-hercules-angkut-alat-kesehatan-corona-dari-shanghai|title=TNI Kerahkan Hercules Angkut Alat Kesehatan Corona dari Shanghai|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/20/covid-19-indonesian-military-to-get-medical-equipment-from-china.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesian military to get medical equipment from China|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n* One person died after having a fever and headaches. The victim, a Russian citizen, died in his boarding house on Jalan Bukit Tunggal Gang 5, West Denpasar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.balipost.com/news/2020/03/21/111174/Sempat-Demam,Warga-Rusia-Ditemukan...html|title=Sempat Demam, Warga Rusia Ditemukan Meninggal|last=POST|first=BALI|date=March 21, 2020|publisher=[[Bali Post Media Group]]|website=BALI POST PORTAL BERITA|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 81 new cases, totalling 450 cases of COVID-19 infection. Indonesia also announced 20 recovered and 38 deaths, an increase of 6 deaths since 20 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4948271/data-terbaru-kasus-positif-corona-jadi-450-bertambah-81|title=Data Terbaru: Kasus Positif Corona Jadi 450, Bertambah 81|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n===22 March===\n* [[:id:Ikatan Dokter Indonesia|Indonesia Medical Association]] (IDI) announced 6 doctors (Dr. Toni Daniel Silitonga; Dr. Ucok Martin; Dr. Djoko Judodjoko; Dr. Hadio Ali; Dr. Laurentius P; Dr. Adi Mirsaputra) have contracted COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4949139/6-dokter-indonesia-jadi-korban-pandemi-corona-ini-daftarnya|title=6 Dokter Indonesia Jadi Korban Pandemi Corona, Ini Daftarnya|last=Mahardhika|first=Anjar|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 64 new cases, a total of 514 cases.\n\n===23 March===\n* Indonesia announced 65 new cases, bringing the total to 579 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4950124/per-23-maret-kasus-positif-corona-di-indonesia-jadi-579|title=Per 23 Maret, Kasus Positif Corona di Indonesia Jadi 579|last=Ibrahim|first=Gibran Maulana|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n*President Joko Widodo inaugurated the first COVID-19 makeshift hospital in the country at the [[Kemayoran Athletes Village|former athlete's village for the 2018 Asian Games]] in [[Kemayoran]], Jakarta. It was slated to be fitted with 3000 beds for patients requiring isolation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/23/09435921/presiden-jokowi-resmikan-rs-darurat-corona-di-wisma-atlet-kemayoran|title=Presiden Jokowi Resmikan RS Darurat Corona di Wisma Atlet Kemayoran|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4949291/dipermak-jadi-rs-hari-ini-wisma-atlet-siap-diisi-pasien-corona|title=Dipermak Jadi RS, Hari Ini Wisma Atlet Siap Diisi Pasien Corona|last=Hamdani|first=Trio|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> Later reports suggested that it would house only 1,800 beds for the first phase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/as-testing-expands-patients-at-indonesias-athletes-village-turn-hospital-expected-to|title=As coronavirus testing expands, cases at Indonesia's athlete's village-turned-hospital expected to rise dramatically|last=hermesauto|date=2020-03-25|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\n===24 March===\n* President Joko Widodo announced the cancellation of the annual national examination (''[[National Exam (Indonesia)|Ujian Nasional]]'') for all education levels, except Vocational High School (''Sekolah Menengah Kejuruan, SMK'') that has been done in almost half of all schools in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951217/jokowi-putuskan-tiadakan-un-2020-imbas-corona|title=Jokowi Putuskan Tiadakan UN 2020 Imbas Corona|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tirto.id/murid-smk-sudah-telanjur-un-nadiem-maaf-kalau-kalian-kecewa-eHlA|title=Murid SMK Sudah Telanjur UN, Nadiem: Maaf Kalau Kalian Kecewa|last=Friana|first=Hendra|website=tirto.id|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951361/un-2020-batal-untuk-sma-sudah-kelar-47-untuk-smk|title=UN 2020 Batal untuk SMA, Sudah Kelar 47% untuk SMK|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> He also announced measures to ease motorcycle loans for one year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951070/jokowi-tukang-ojek-jangan-khawatir-cicilan-motor-dilonggarkan-1-tahun|title=Jokowi: Tukang Ojek Jangan Khawatir, Cicilan Motor Dilonggarkan 1 Tahun|last=Erwanti|first=Marlinda Oktavia|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n* Indonesia confirmed 107 more cases, 686 in total.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200324154310-4-147291/bertambah-107-total-positif-corona-di-ri-686-kasus|title=Bertambah 107, Total Positif Corona di RI 686 Kasus|last=Sandi|first=Ferry|date=|website=CNBC Indonesia|language=id-ID|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n===25 March===\n* The [[Ministry of Transportation (Indonesia)|Indonesian Ministry of Transportation]] discouraged everyone from travelling home for the [[Eid al-Fitr]] holiday to contain the spread of the virus.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sugianto |first1=Danang |title=Kemenhub Minta Masyarakat Tidak Mudik, Lebaran Bisa Video Call |url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4952578/kemenhub-minta-masyarakat-tidak-mudik-lebaran-bisa-video-call?tag_from=wp_beritautama&_ga=2.107555403.834036946.1583960210-317182638.1583477810 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |publisher=detik.com |language=id-ID|date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Indonesia confirmed 105 more cases and corrected the data from the previous day. It should have said 685, while the previous day's data recorded 686. One patient's name was mistakenly registered in two hospitals. The total number of cases becomes 790.\n\n===26 March===\n* Indonesia announced 103 new cases, bringing the total number to 893.\n* Researchers have estimated that there could be tens of thousands of hidden infections across the country.<ref name=\"FirdausRatcliffe\">{{Cite news|last=Firdaus|first=Febriana|last2=Ratcliffe|first2=Rebecca|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2020/mar/26/indonesia-could-have-thousands-of-hidden-coronavirus-cases-study-says|title=Indonesia's hidden coronavirus cases threaten to overwhelm hospitals|date=2020-03-26|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-27|url-status=live|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n*40 tonnes of medical equipment from China transported to Jakarta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kumparan.com/kumparannews/40-ton-bantuan-alkes-dari-china-diangkut-garuda-tiba-di-jakarta-malam-ini-1t6Jh6wihWO|title=40 Ton Bantuan Alkes dari China Diangkut Garuda, Tiba di Jakarta Malam Ini|website=kumparan|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\n===27 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed 153 new positive cases, 1,046 in total. They also announced 9 deaths and 11 recoveries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kompas.com/tren/read/2020/03/27/193000465/update--rincian-kasus-virus-corona-di-28-provinsi-di-indonesia-dan-upaya|title=Update: Rincian Kasus Virus Corona di 28 Provinsi di Indonesia dan Upaya Pemerintah|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*[[Beringharjo]] and Tanah Abang (10 days) markets are closed to prevent COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/ekonomi/20200327161431-92-487587/cegah-corona-pasar-batik-beringharjo-yogyakarta-tutup|title=Cegah Corona, Pasar Batik Beringharjo Yogyakarta Tutup|website=ekonomi|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/27/safety-above-all-tanah-abang-market-closes-for-10-days-faces-ramadan-losses-amid-covid-19.html|title=Safety above all: Tanah Abang market closes for 10 days, faces Ramadan losses amid COVID-19|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*[[Coordinating Ministry for Political, Legal, and Security Affairs (Indonesia)|Coordinating Minister for Political, Legal, and Security Affairs of Indonesia]] [[Mahfud MD]] said that a special law about local lockdown is currently in the works.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Arkyasa |first1=Mahinda |title=Mahfud MD: Govt' Prepares Regulation on Local Quarantine |url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1324774/mahfud-md-govt-prepares-regulation-on-local-quarantine |accessdate=28 March 2020 |publisher=Tempo |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===28 March===\n* Indonesia announced 109 more cases, bringing the total number to 1,155.\n* A number of cities decided to issue local lockdowns, such as [[Tegal (city)|the city of Tegal]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Suherdjoko |title=Tegal blocks roads into city in first attempt to impose lockdown in Indonesia |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/26/tegal-blocks-roads-into-city-in-first-attempt-to-impose-lockdown-in-indonesia.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=26 March 2020}}</ref> in Central Java and the province of Papua.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mawel |first1=Benny |title=Papua restricts entry as concerns mount over lack of facilities to treat COVID-19 |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/25/papua-restricts-entry-as-concerns-mount-over-lack-of-facilities-to-treat-covid-19.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Indonesia AirAsia]] suspends all flights from 1 April until at least 21 April for domestic flights and 17 May for international flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=AirAsia Indonesia suspends all flights starting April 1 |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/travel/2020/03/28/airasia-indonesia-suspends-all-flights-starting-april-1.html |accessdate=30 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===29 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed another 130 new cases, 1,285 in total.\n* The state railway company [[Kereta Api Indonesia]] cancels 28 routes from Jakarta for the month of April.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ramadhian |first1=Nabilla |title=28 Kereta Api Jarak Jauh dari Gambir, Pasar Senen, dan Jakarta Kota Dibatalkan |url=https://travel.kompas.com/read/2020/03/29/112741327/28-kereta-api-jarak-jauh-dari-gambir-pasar-senen-dan-jakarta-kota-dibatalkan |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=Kompas |publisher=Kompas}}</ref>\n\n===30 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed 129 new cases, bringing the total number to 1,414.\n*Jokowi orders large-scale social restrictions coupled with 'civil emergency' policies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/30/jokowi-orders-large-scale-social-restrictions-coupled-with-civil-emergency-policies.html|title=Jokowi orders large-scale social restrictions coupled with 'civil emergency' policies|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n===31 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed 114 new cases, 1,528 in total.\n* President [[Joko Widodo]] declared public health emergency and invoked the police to enforce large-scale social distancing policy <ref>{{cite news |title=Jokowi declares COVID-19 health emergency, imposes large-scale social restrictions |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/jokowi-declares-covid-19-health-emergency-imposes-large-scale-social-restrictions.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>, in addition to allocating IDR 405 trillion for eradication of COVID-19 and cushioning of social and economical effects due to the pandemic, and announced stimulus for the low-middle class society. <ref>{{cite news |last1=Gorbiano |first1=Marchio Irfan |title=Indonesia announces Rp 405 trillion COVID-19 budget, anticipates 5% deficit in historic move |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/indonesia-announces-rp-405-trillion-covid-19-budget-anticipates-5-deficit-in-historic-move.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Harsono |first1=Norman |title=Jokowi announces free electricity, discounts for households hardest hit by COVID-19 impacts |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/jokowi-announces-free-electricity-discounts-for-households-hardest-hit-by-covid-19-impacts.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== April ==\n\n=== 1 April ===\n\n* Indonesia confirmed 149 new cases, bringing the total number to 1,677.\n*300 police students at [[:id:Sekolah_Pembentukan_Perwira|Sekolah Pembentukan Perwira]] (Setukpa) [[:id:Lembaga_Pendidikan_dan_Pelatihan_Kepolisian_Negara_Republik_Indonesia|Lembaga Pendidikan Polri]] (Lemdikpol) in [[Sukabumi]] are quarantined for 14 days after positive rapid test results.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/04/01/18562421/300-polisi-yang-rapid-test-nya-positif-dikarantina-14-hari|title=300 Polisi yang \"Rapid Test\"-nya Positif Dikarantina 14 Hari|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ayobandung.com/read/2020/04/01/84615/positif-corona-300-polisi-setukpa-lemdikpol-di-sukabumi-diisolasi|title=Positif Corona, 300 Polisi Setukpa Lemdikpol di Sukabumi Diisolasi|last=Network|first=Ayo Media|date=2020-04-01|website=AyoBandung.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n===2 April===\n* Indonesia confirmed 113 new cases, 1,790 in total.\n* Indonesia has now banned foreigners from entering its border. Its citizens returning from abroad have to provide health report and do compulsory self-quarantine.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesia-imposes-entry-ban-on-foreigners-makes-quarantine-compulsory-for-returning-citizens\n|title=Indonesia Banned Foreigners From Entering Its Border\n|author=Lenny Tristia Tambun\n|work=Jakarta Globe\n|date=31 March 2020\n|accessdate=3 April 2020\n}}</ref>\n* Indonesia's Justice and Human Rights Ministry will release more than 30,000 prisoners to avoid mass coronavirus infections in Indonesia's overcrowded jails. It received a lot of critics especially for those who did corruption. However, it was declared that they will not release prisoners convicted for corruption, illegal logging, terrorism, drug crimes, gross human rights crimes or transnational organized crimes.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesia-releases-30000-prisoners-as-covid19-cases-double-in-a-week\n|title=Indonesia Releases 30,000 Prisoners as COVID-19 Cases Double in a Week\n|author=Nur Yasmin\n|work=Jakarta Globe\n|date=2 April 2020\n|accessdate=7 April 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n===3 April===\n* Indonesia confirmed 196 new cases, bringing the total number to 1,986.\n\n===4 April===\n* Indonesia announced 106 new cases, 2,092 in total.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beritasatu.com/nasional/616711-bertambah-106-orang-kasus-positif-corona-di-indonesia-menjadi-2092|title=Bertambah 106 Orang, Kasus Positif Corona di Indonesia Menjadi 2.092|last=BeritaSatu.com|website=beritasatu.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\n===5 April===\n* Indonesia confirmed 181 new cases, bringing the total number to 2,273.\n\n===6 April===\n\n* Indonesia had tested 11,242 specimens, in which 8,000 were negative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4967066/11242-spesimen-diperiksa-8000-orang-di-antaranya-negatif-corona|title=11.242 Spesimen Diperiksa, 8.000 Orang di Antaranya Negatif Corona|last=Erwanti|first=Marlinda Oktavia|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 218 additional cases, 2,491 in total.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.detik.com/news/berita/d-4967047/kasus-positif-corona-di-indonesia-jadi-2491-per-6-april|title=Kasus Positif Corona di Indonesia Jadi 2.491 Per 6 April|last=Gibran|first=Maulana Ibrahim|date=|website=detiknews|language=Id|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n===7 April===\n* Indonesia confirmed 247 new cases, 2,738 in total.\n*The Jakarta administration has revealed it has buried 639 people according to the protocols for burial of people either suspected of or confirmed as having been infected with COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/04/07/jakarta-buries-639-bodies-according-to-covid-19-protocols.html|title=Jakarta buries 639 bodies according to COVID-19 protocols|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n*Health Ministry grants Jakarta's request to impose large-scale social restrictions start from 10 April until 24 April and can be extended for 14 days after last COVID-19 case. The ministry wrote in a ministerial decree that data had shown a significant increase in, and a rapid spread of, COVID-19 cases, accompanied by evidence of local transmission in Jakarta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/04/07/no-access-limitation-to-or-from-jakarta-despite-social-restrictions-police-say.html|title=No access limitation to or from Jakarta despite social restrictions, police say|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2020/04/07/15441281/psbb-di-jakarta-berlaku-hingga-20-april-dan-bisa-diperpanjang|title=PSBB di Jakarta Berlaku hingga 20 April dan Bisa Diperpanjang|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200407152446-20-491265/anies-resmi-terapkan-psbb-di-dki-jakarta-jumat-10-april-2020|title=Anies Resmi Terapkan PSBB di DKI Jakarta Jumat 10 April 2020|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n*Only 36 in every million people are being tested for the coronavirus in Indonesia, making it the fourth worst in testing rate among countries with a 50 million population or above. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/04/07/indonesia-ranks-among-worlds-worst-in-coronavirus-testing-rate.html|title=Indonesia ranks among world's worst in coronavirus testing rate|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n===8 April===\n* Indonesia confirmed 218 new cases, bringing the total number to 2,956\n\n===9 April===\n* Indonesia announced 337 additional cases, 3,293 in total.\n* Gorontalo announced its first case. By 9 April night, cases have been confirmed in all provinces in Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/04/10/07285901/gubernur-gorontalo-umumkan-kasus-pertama-positif-corona|title=Gubernur Gorontalo Umumkan Kasus Pertama Positif Corona|last=Azhar|first=Rosyid A|website=Kompas|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n*The Public Works and Public Housing Ministry prepared three additional towers (tower 2, 4, and 5) at Wisma Atlet makeshift hospital to add COVID-19 patient rooms and provide a decent place for doctors and paramedics who work 24 hours. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1330090/govt-sets-3-more-towers-at-wisma-atlet-for-covid-19-hospital|title=Govt Sets 3 More Towers at Wisma Atlet for Covid-19 Hospital|last=Afifa|first=Laila|date=2020-04-10|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n*Online ride-hailing company Gojek and digital healthcare company [https://www.halodoc.com/ Halodoc] were set to hold free rapid tests to detect the coronavirus (COVID-19) for the public as initial screenings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1329893/halodoc-gojek-set-to-hold-free-covid-19-rapid-tests|title=Halodoc, Gojek Set to Hold Free COVID-19 Rapid Tests|last=Afifa|first=Laila|date=2020-04-09|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n===10 April===\n* Indonesia confirmed 219 new cases, 3,512 in total.\n*Online ride-hailing companies, [[Gojek|GoJek]] and [[Grab (company)|Grab]], no longer provide motorcycle taxi (ojek) service on its apps as Jakarta starts imposing the large-scale social restriction policy. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1330115/psbb-jakarta-gojek-grab-scrape-ojek-service|title=PSBB Jakarta; Gojek, Grab Scrape 'Ojek' Service|last=Afifa|first=Laila|date=2020-04-10|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n*Indonesia had tested 19,500 specimens based on [[Polymerase chain reaction|Polymerase Chain Reaction]] method.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/04/10/19164501/ri-sudah-periksa-19500-orang-lewat-tes-pcr-terkait-covid-19|title=RI sudah Periksa 19.500 Orang lewat Tes PCR Terkait Covid-19|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n===11 April===\n* Indonesia announced 330 new cases, bringing the total number to 3,842.\n* Preemployment card was launched to help those who are in economy difficulty due to the pandemic.\n\n===12 April===\n\n* Indonesia had tested 27,000 specimens.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4974227/pemerintah-sudah-periksa-lebih-dari-27-ribu-orang-melalui-tes-pcr|title=Pemerintah Sudah Periksa Lebih dari 27 Ribu Orang Melalui Tes PCR|last=Safitri|first=Eva|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n* Large-scale social restrictions will be in effect in [[Depok]] municipality, [[Bogor]] municipality and regency, and [[Bekasi]] municipality and regency from 15 April for at least two weeks.<ref>{{cite news |title=Satellite cities gear up as Health Ministry green lights PSBB request |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/04/12/satellite-cities-gear-up-as-health-ministry-green-lights-psbb-request.html |accessdate=12 April 2020 |agency=The Jakarta Post |date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 399 additional cases, the most in a single day since the pandemic began in Indonesia. The total number now is 4,241. 73 patients recovered while 46 deceased.\n\n==See also==\n* [[2020 in Indonesia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Indonesia|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Timeline of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Indonesia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Sequence of major events in ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Indonesia}}\n{{Current event|date=April 2020}}\nThis article documents the timeline of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia|coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia]].\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Indonesia medical cases chart}}\n\n==February==\n\n===2 February===\n* The Indonesian government evacuated 243 Indonesian nationals from [[Wuhan]], [[China]]. The repatriated Indonesians were placed under quarantine in the [[Natuna Regency|Natuna Islands]] but were not tested as they were asymptomatic.<ref name=\"Feb2020\">{{cite web \n|title=Indonesian Government Successfully Repatriated 243 People From Wuhan China {{!}} Portal Kementerian Luar Negeri Republik Indonesia \n|url=https://kemlu.go.id/portal/en/read/1011/berita/indonesian-government-successfully-repatriated-243-people-from-wuhan-china \n|website=kemlu.go.id \n|publisher=MINISTRY OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS OF THE REPUBLIC OF INDONESIA \n|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2020/03/indonesia-finally-reports-two-coronavirus-cases-scientists-worry-it-has-many-more|first=Dyna|last= Rochmyaningsih|date=3 March 2020|title=Indonesia finally reports two coronavirus cases. Scientists worry it has many more|work=American Association for the Advancement of Science|accessdate=3 March 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n===24 February===\n* 9 Indonesians on board the ''[[Diamond Princess (ship)|Diamond Princess]]'' tested positive for the virus and were moved to treatment facilities in [[Japan]]. The Indonesian government repatriated and then quarantined the remaining 68 crew members, along with the 188 from the ''[[World Dream]]'', onto the uninhabited Sebaru Kecil Island in the [[Thousand Islands (Indonesia)|Thousand Islands]] off the coast of [[Jakarta]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/24/number-of-indonesians-with-coronavirus-on-diamond-princess-rises-to-nine.html\n|title=Number of Indonesians with coronavirus on Diamond Princess rises to nine\n|author1=Marchio Irfan Gorbiano\n|author2=Budi Sutrisno \n|work=The Jakarta Post\n|date=2020-02-24\n|accessdate=2020-03-05\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200224144659-4-140074/wni-kena-corona-di-kapal-diamond-princess-kini-jadi-9-orang \n|title=WNI Kena Corona di Kapal Diamond Princess Kini Jadi 9 orang\n|trans-title=Indonesian Citizens Affected by Corona on the Diamond Princess Ship are now 9 people\n|work=CNBC Indonesia\n|date=24 February 2020\n|accessdate=24 February 2020\n|language=id\n|url-status=live\n}}</ref>\n\n==March==\n\n[[File:CoViD-19 ID.svg|thumb|upright=2|left|Number of cases (blue) and number of deaths (red) on a [[logarithmic scale]].]]\n\n===2 March===\n* President [[Joko Widodo]] confirmed the first two cases of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] in the country in a televised statement.<ref name=\"straitstimes\">{{cite news |author=Linda Yulisman |title=Mother and daughter test positive for coronavirus in Indonesia, first confirmed cases in the country |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/indonesia-confirms-two-coronavirus-cases-president |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=The Straits Times |issue=Asia |date=2 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> According to the Minister of Health [[Terawan Agus Putranto]], the patients contracted the virus from an infected Japanese person in [[Depok]] who later tested positive in [[Malaysia]].<ref name=\"theguardian-ratcliffe\" /> Both Indonesian patients were subsequently hospitalized at Sulianti Saroso Infection Center Hospital, [[North Jakarta]].\n\n===6 March===\n* As of 6 March, Indonesia had only tested 450 individuals out of its 270 million population.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://infeksiemerging.kemkes.go.id/uncategorized/situasi-terkini-perkembangan-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-6-maret-2020\n|title=Situasi Terkini Perkembangan Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) 6 Maret 2020\n|work=Info Infeksi Emerging Kementerian Kesehatan RI\n|language=id\n|date=2020-03-06\n|accessdate=2020-03-06\n}}</ref>\n\n===7 March===\n* One of the crew evacuated from the ''Diamond Princess'' was suspected of contracting the disease and was subsequently transferred to an isolation unit at Persahabatan Central General Hospital, [[East Jakarta]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/another-diamond-princess-crew-member-from-indonesia-suspected-of-contracting-coronavirus|title=Another Diamond Princess Crew Member From Indonesia Suspected of Contracting Coronavirus|website=Jakarta Globe|date=2020-03-06|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n===8 March===\n* A 50-year-old woman from Jakarta tested positive in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]. She began showing symptoms two days after flying to [[Perth]] from Jakarta on 27 February and saw a GP four days after arriving in Melbourne on 2 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/victoria/indonesian-woman-becomes-12th-victorian-covid-19-case-20200308-p54809.html|title=Indonesian woman becomes 12th Victorian COVID-19 case|work=The Age|language=en|date=2020-03-08|accessdate=2020-03-08|first=Tate|last=Papworth}}</ref>\n* The government of Indonesia announced two more confirmed cases. One patient was infected through close contact with case #1, the other patient being a crew member of the Diamond Princess.<ref name=\"8Mar20\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200308162030-20-481536/pasien-positif-virus-corona-bertambah-jadi-6-orang|title=Pasien Positif Corona Bertambah Jadi 6 Orang|work=CNN Indonesia|language=id|date=2020-03-08|accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n===9 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed 13 new cases of COVID-19 infection, 2 of them being foreigners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4931659/melonjak-pasien-positif-corona-di-wilayah-ri-jadi-19-orang|title=Melonjak! Pasien Positif Corona di Wilayah RI Jadi 19 Orang|author=Andhika Prasetia |website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-09|date=2020-03-09}}</ref> The Indonesian government decided not to disclose the detection location of the patient and the treatment facility used.{{citation  needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n===10 March===\n* 2 patients who were previously confirmed to be positive were subsequently reported as negative, substantiating an explanation made by an Indonesian government representative. The two patients were to be discharged, should further test confirm their negative status.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/internasional/d-4932718/kabar-baik-pasien-kasus-06-dan-14-sudah-negatif-corona|title=Kabar Baik! Pasien Kasus 06 dan 14 Sudah Negatif Corona|author=Kadek Melda Luxiana|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-10|date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n*Indonesia confirmed 8 new cases of COVID-19 infection, 2 of them foreigners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4933267/jadi-27-orang-ini-detail-8-pasien-baru-virus-corona|title=Jadi 27 Orang, Ini Detail 8 Pasien Baru Virus Corona|author=Kadek Melda Luxiana|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-10|date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n*A suspected COVID-19 patient fleed from Persahabatan Central General Hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4937896/pasien-positif-corona-kabur-dari-rs-persahabatan-dijemput-keluarga|title=Pasien Positif Corona Kabur dari RS Persahabatan, Dijemput Keluarga|last=Luqman|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4937970/alasan-pasien-positif-corona-kabur-tak-mau-sekamar-isolasi-berdua|title=Alasan Pasien Positif Corona Kabur: Tak Mau Sekamar Isolasi Berdua|last=Arunata|first=Luqman Nurhadi|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref> She was later confirmed as positive of the virus and has returned to the hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4938404/pasien-corona-yang-sempat-kabur-dipastikan-sudah-kembali-ke-rs-persahabatan|title=Pasien Corona yang Sempat Kabur Dipastikan Sudah Kembali ke RS Persahabatan|last=Luxiana|first=Kadek Melda|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===11 March===\n* Case #25 died due to complications of the disease.<ref name=death>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/11/13061741/breaking-news-satu-pasien-covid-19-di-indonesia-meninggal-dunia|title=BREAKING NEWS: Satu Pasien Covid-19 di Indonesia Meninggal Dunia|author=Ihsanuddin|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-11|date=2020-03-11}}</ref> The victim was a British national and died in [[Bali]]'s hospital.<ref name=death2/>\n*Indonesia confirmed 7 new cases of COVID-19 infection, all of them imported cases.<ref name=:34>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4934881/pasien-positif-virus-corona-jadi-34-orang-2-sembuh-1-meninggal|title=Pasien Positif Virus Corona Jadi 34 Orang: 2 Sembuh, 1 Meninggal|author=Kanavino Ahmad Rizqo |website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref>\n\n===12 March===\n* 5 cases recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4936834/data-terbaru-corona-terkait-indonesia-12-maret-2020-pukul-2100-wib/3|title=Data Terbaru Corona Terkait Indonesia, 12 Maret 2020 Pukul 21.00 WIB|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|date=2020-03-12|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n*[[:id:Daftar Menteri Ketenagakerjaan Indonesia|Indonesian Labour Minister]] [[:id:Ida Fauziyah|Ida Fauziah]] mandated that all Indonesian companies provide their employees with coronavirus prevention equipment, such as face masks and hand sanitizer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4935342/perusahaan-wajib-sediakan-masker-demi-cegah-corona|title=Perusahaan Wajib Sediakan Masker Demi Cegah Corona|last=Indraini|first=Anisa|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===13 March===\n* 3 coronavirus-linked deaths were reported, 1 case in [[Surakarta|Solo]], [[Central Java]].<ref name=death3>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kompas.com/tren/read/2020/03/13/120826665/satu-pasien-isolasi-yang-meninggal-di-rsud-moewardi-solo-positif-corona|title=Satu Pasien Isolasi yang Meninggal di RSUD Moewardi Solo Positif Corona|author=Labib Zamani|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-13|date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4937577/ini-detail-pasien-virus-corona-yang-meninggal-di-solo|title=Ini Detail Pasien Virus Corona yang Meninggal di Solo|author=Firdaus Anwar|website=Detik.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-13|date=2020-03-13}}</ref> The other two were undisclosed.<ref name=\"Andhika Prasetia\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4938023/kasus-positif-corona-di-ri-jadi-69|title=Kasus Positif Corona di RI Jadi 69|author=Andhika Prasetia|website=Detik.com|date=2020-03-13|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4938060/total-4-pasien-positif-corona-meninggal-dunia|title=Total 4 Pasien Positif Corona Meninggal Dunia|author=Zunita Putri|website=Detik.com|date=2020-03-13|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n* Indonesia confirmed 35 new cases of COVID-19 infection, totalling 69 cases.<ref name=\"Andhika Prasetia\"/>\n* The first affected medical worker died on 13 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/14/18404141/yurianto-ada-petugas-medis-positif-corona-yang-meninggal-dunia|title=Yurianto: Ada Petugas Medis Positif Corona yang Meninggal Dunia|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14|date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===14 March===\n* The Indonesian government confirmed 27 new cases of COVID-19, a total of 96 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4939115/ada-27-kasus-baru-pasien-positif-corona-di-indonesia-jadi-96-orang|title=Ada 27 Kasus Baru, Pasien Positif Corona di Indonesia Jadi 96 Orang|last=Rahayu|first=Lisye Sri|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> \n* This date also marks the first time that the government announced the locations with confirmed coronavirus cases. Locations with confirmed coronavirus cases included every district in [[Jakarta]], [[Tangerang]] in [[Banten]], [[Bandung]] in [[West Java]], [[Surakarta|Solo]] in [[Central Java]], [[Yogyakarta]] in [[Special Region of Yogyakarta]], [[Pontianak, West Kalimantan|Pontianak]] in [[West Kalimantan]], [[Manado]] in [[North Sulawesi]] and [[Bali]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Daerah yang Terdapat Positif Corona: dari Bandung ke Manado|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200314164544-20-483432/daerah-yang-terdapat-positif-corona-dari-bandung-ke-manado|publisher=CNN Indonesia|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n* 3 further patients recovered, for a total of 8 recovered patients.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/14/16452961/update-tambah-3-total-8-orang-sembuh-dari-corona-di-indonesia|title=UPDATE: Tambah 3, Total 8 Orang Sembuh dari Corona di Indonesia|author=Ihsanuddin |website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14|date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n* 1 patient died, bringing the total to 5 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939143/pasien-meninggal-akibat-corona-di-ri-bertambah-jadi-5|title=Pasien Meninggal Akibat Corona di RI Bertambah Jadi 5|author=Rahel Narda Chatrine|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14|date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n* [[Ministry of Transportation (Indonesia)|Indonesian Minister of Transportation]], [[Budi Karya Sumadi]] tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939392/menhub-budi-karya-pasien-positif-corona-kasus-76|title=Menhub Budi Karya Pasien Positif Corona Kasus 76|author=Andhika Prasetia|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Menhub Budi Karya Sumadi positif COVID-19 |url=https://www.antaranews.com/berita/1356658/menhub-budi-karya-sumadi-positif-covid-19|language=id |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=Antara News |date=14 March 2020}}</ref> A few days prior, on 10 March, Budi Karya was diagnosed with typhoid fever after travelling to [[Wakatobi Regency|Wakatobi]], [[Toraja]], [[Luwuk]], [[Makassar]], [[Parepare]], [[Kertajati International Airport|Kertajati]], and [[Indramayu]]. His travel history included travel to [[Kertajati International Airport]] on 1 March that had acted as an evacuation centre for the repatriated crew of the Diamond Princess. One of the crew of Diamond Princess tested positive for COVID-19 on 8 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4933161/menhub-jatuh-sakit-jubir-kena-gejala-tifus|title=Menhub Jatuh Sakit, Jubir: Kena Gejala Tifus|last=Prasetia|first=Andhika|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> On 11 March, Budi had also met with the Dutch Minister of Infrastructure and Water Management [[Cora van Nieuwenhuizen|Cora Van Nieuwenhuize]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939440/menhub-sempat-ke-istana-bertemu-pejabat-belanda-sebelum-positif-corona|title=Menhub Sempat ke Istana-Bertemu Pejabat Belanda Sebelum Positif Corona|last=Prasetia|first=Andhika|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\n===15 March===\n* Indonesia confirmed 21 new cases of COVID-19 infection, 19 in [[Jakarta]] and 2 in [[Central Java]], a total of 117 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200315133445-20-483573/21-kasus-baru-pasien-positif-corona-indonesia-jadi-117-orang|title=21 Kasus Baru, Pasien Positif Corona Indonesia Jadi 117 Orang|work=CNN Indonesia|language=id|date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939844/pasien-positif-corona-bertambah-21-kasus-total-jadi-117-kasus|title=Pasien Positif Corona Bertambah 21 Kasus, Total Jadi 117 Kasus|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15|date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n*Indonesian President [[Joko Widodo]] is said to be undergoing a COVID-19 test in the evening.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939909/presiden-jokowi-jalani-tes-virus-corona-sore-ini|title=Presiden Jokowi Jalani Tes Virus Corona Sore Ini|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15|date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n===16 March===\n* Indonesian Vice-President [[Ma'ruf Amin]] and Indonesian Interior Minister [[Tito Karnavian]] have tested negative on the COVID-19 test.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/16/10390031/sudah-tes-wapres-maruf-amin-negatif-covid-19|title=Sudah Tes, Wapres Ma'ruf Amin Negatif Covid-19|author=Deti Mega Purnamasari|editor=Diamanty Meiliana|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200316140224-4-145183/usai-tes-covid-19-di-rspad-tito-istri-dipastikan-sehat|title=Usai Tes Covid-19 di RSPAD, Tito & Istri Dipastikan Sehat|last=Iqbal|first=Muhammad|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n*Indonesia confirmed 17 new cases of infection, in a total of 134 cases. 14 new cases in Jakarta, 1 new case in Central Java, 1 new case in Banten, and 1 new case in West Java.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4941340/ada-tambahan-17-pasien-corona-baru-14-di-antaranya-dari-jakarta|title=Ada Tambahan 17 Pasien Corona Baru, 14 di Antaranya dari Jakarta|last=Luxiana|first=Kadek Melda|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n*Indonesia announced that it will start to quarantine asymptomatic COVID-19 patients in their own home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4941325/kemenkes-sekarang-pasien-positif-corona-bisa-diisolasi-mandiri-di-rumah|title=Kemenkes: Sekarang Pasien Positif Corona Bisa Diisolasi Mandiri di Rumah|last=Melda|first=Kadek|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n===17 March===\n* In response to the growing number of COVID-19 cases in Indonesia, the [[Indonesian National Board for Disaster Management]] declared an emergency period for 91 days, effective until 29 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pemerintah Tetapkan Masa Darurat Bencana Corona hingga 29 Mei 2020|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942327/pemerintah-tetapkan-masa-darurat-bencana-corona-hingga-29-mei-2020?tag_from=news_mostpop|publisher=Detik|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n* The Indonesian government announced 38 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total number of infections to 172.<ref>{{cite web|title=Data Terbaru Virus Corona: Total Kasus Positif Melonjak Jadi 172|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942786/data-terbaru-virus-corona-total-kasus-positif-melonjak-jadi-172|publisher=Detik|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n*1 case recovered, adding to a total of 9 cases recovered.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4942803/virus-corona-indonesia-jadi-172-kasus-9-sembuh-5-meninggal|title=Virus Corona Indonesia Jadi 172 Kasus, 9 Sembuh 5 Meninggal|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n*2 patients died (1 in Semarang and another one still unknown), in a total of 7 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200317210849-20-484354/pasien-meninggal-akibat-corona-bertambah-jadi-7-orang|title=Pasien Meninggal Akibat Corona Bertambah Jadi 7 Orang|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n*There are mistakes in the counting of the deaths.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://tirto.id/update-corona-di-ri-172-positif-7-meninggal-wni-diminta-pulang-eFLZ | title=Update Corona di RI: 172 Positif, 7 Meninggal & WNI Diminta Pulang}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4943106/gubernur-banten-umumkan-1-warga-positif-corona-meninggal-kemenkes-tak-tahu|title=Gubernur Banten Umumkan 1 Warga Positif Corona Meninggal, Kemenkes Tak Tahu|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> The minister of health reported that the total number of the death is still 5, the same as that on 14 March<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942786/data-terbaru-virus-corona-total-kasus-positif-melonjak-jadi-172?tag_from=wp_cb_mostPopular_list&_ga=2.238927360.105839233.1584339272-1415494084.1580723020|title=Data Terbaru Virus Corona: Total Kasus Positif Melonjak Jadi 172|last=detikcom|first=tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> while two new deaths were reported in the early morning by Governor of Central Java<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-tengah/d-4942759/1-pasien-positif-corona-meninggal-di-rs-kariadi-semarang-hari-ini|title=1 Pasien Positif Corona Meninggal di RS Kariadi Semarang Hari Ini|last=Purbaya|first=Angling Adhitya|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> and Governor of Banten.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942389/gubernur-banten-1-pasien-positif-corona-di-pondok-aren-meninggal|title=Gubernur Banten: 1 Pasien Positif Corona di Pondok Aren Meninggal|last=Komara|first=Indra|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> The total number of deaths should be 7.\n\n===18 March===\n*Indonesia confirmed 55 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total up to 227 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944276/update-terbaru-virus-corona-di-indonesia-total-kasus-positif-jadi-227-orang|title=Update Terbaru Virus Corona di Indonesia: Total Kasus Positif Jadi 227 Orang|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n*12 patients died, the number of deaths has now increased to 19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944358/pernyataan-lengkap-pemerintah-soal-227-kasus-positif-corona-dan-19-meninggal|title=Pernyataan Lengkap Pemerintah soal 227 Kasus Positif Corona dan 19 Meninggal|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> The 19 fatalities mean that Indonesia has now recorded the highest death toll among Southeast Asian countries hit by the coronavirus to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/18/covid-19-indonesia-records-highest-death-toll-in-southeast-asia-at-19.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesia records highest death toll in Southeast Asia at 19|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Indonesia's case fatality rate has reached 8.37% which is double the world case fatality rate (4.07%).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944800/tingkat-kematian-pasien-corona-di-ri-837-bagaimana-negara-lain|title=Tingkat Kematian Pasien Corona di RI 8,37%, Bagaimana Negara Lain?|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n*7 Indonesians in [[India]] tested positive for COVID-19 were a part of a 10-member team who travelled to [[Karimnagar]] for a religious tour.<ref name=\"TH1\">{{cite news |last1=Geetanath |first1=K. Shiva Shankar & V. |title=Coronavirus {{!}} Telangana reports 8 new COVID-19 cases |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/telangana-reports-8-new-covid-19-cases/article31102733.ece?homepage=true |newspaper=The Hindu |language=en-IN |date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*After 2 positive cases, Governor of West Kalimantan [[Sutarmidji]] declares an \"extraordinary event\" until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4944658/ada-2-kasus-positif-gubernur-tetapkan-kalbar-klb-corona|title=Ada 2 Kasus Positif, Gubernur Tetapkan Kalbar KLB Corona|last=Kholid|first=Idham|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n===19 March===\n* Joko Widodo announces 7 critical points (mass rapid tests, incentive for medical personnel, involve religious people, stop exporting medical equipment, stop holiday, incentive for small and medium enterprises, increase food stocks) to accelerate the elimination of COVID-19 outbreak in Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4945259/ini-arahan-lengkap-terbaru-jokowi-untuk-tangani-virus-corona|title=Ini Arahan Lengkap Terbaru Jokowi untuk Tangani Virus Corona|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=LIVE : Rapat Terbatas Laporan Tim Gugus Tugas COVID-19, Istana Merdeka, 19 Maret 2020|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NnpUlfKq74U|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/19/15282081/7-arahan-terbaru-jokowi-untuk-penanganan-covid-19|title=7 Arahan Terbaru Jokowi untuk Penanganan Covid-19 Halaman all|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*Indonesia announced 82 new cases, bringing the total to 309 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/19/15531171/update-total-pasien-covid-19-di-indonesia-kini-309-kasus|title=UPDATE: Total Pasien Covid-19 di Indonesia Kini 309 Kasus|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4945783/kasus-wni-positif-corona-melonjak-dari-227-jadi-309|title=Kasus WNI Positif Corona Melonjak dari 227 Jadi 309|last=Sidik|first=Farih Maulana|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> However, it is revised to 308 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200319182124-4-146252/pemerintah-meralat-kasus-positif-corona-di-ri-jadi-308-kasus|title=Pemerintah Meralat: Kasus Positif Corona di RI Jadi 308 Kasus|last=dob|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*4 more patients in DKI Jakarta announced cured from COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/19/16104301/update-15-orang-dinyatakan-sembuh-dari-covid-19|title=UPDATE: 15 Orang Dinyatakan Sembuh dari Covid-19|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*The import of Rapid Test Tools (15 minutes - 3 hours) by [[:id:Rajawali Nusantara Indonesia|Rajawali Nusantara Indonesia]] from China has been approved by [[Ministry of Health (Indonesia)|Ministry of Health]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4945868/alat-cek-virus-corona-15-menit-mulai-masuk-ke-ri-hari-ini|title=Alat Cek Virus Corona 15 Menit Mulai Masuk ke RI Hari Ini|last=Afriyadi|first=Achmad Dwi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4944943/ri-mau-beli-alat-tes-corona-secepat-kilat-buatan-china|title=RI Mau Beli Alat Tes Corona 'Secepat Kilat' Buatan China|last=Afriyadi|first=Achmad Dwi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n* President Joko Widodo and wife, [[Iriana]], tested negative on the COVID-19 test.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4945942/jokowi-saya-dan-ibu-iriana-alhamdulillah-negatif-corona|title=Jokowi: Saya dan Ibu Iriana Alhamdulillah Negatif Corona|last=Erwanti|first=Marlinda Oktavia|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n* Indonesian Chief of Police [[Idham Azis]] publishes notice for all policeman to disperse crowds anywhere at anytime, including restaurants, matrimony and religious services, and to deny permits for large events.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Putra |first1=Nanda Permana |title=Isi Maklumat Kapolri Terkait Corona yang Buat Kapolsek Kembangan Dicopot |url=https://www.liputan6.com/news/read/4217314/isi-maklumat-kapolri-terkait-corona-yang-buat-kapolsek-kembangan-dicopot |accessdate=3 April 2020 |publisher=Liputan6.com |date=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n* The government cancelled a [[Tablighi Jamaat]] event in the [[Gowa Regency]] in [[Sulawesi]]. Thousands had already gathered despite a call for it to be cancelled earlier. A similar gathering in Kuala Lumpur in late February had caused a large outbreak of Covid-19 cases in Malaysia including 3 Indonesians.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2020/03/19/indonesia-cancels-international-muslim-gathering-as-virus-risk-mounts |title= Indonesia cancels international Muslim gathering as virus risk mounts |date= 19 March 2020|work=The Star}}</ref>\n\n===20 March===\n* Indonesia announced 60 new cases, bringing the total to 369 cases. Indonesia also announced 17 recovered and 32 deaths, an increase of 7 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947188/data-terbaru-369-positif-corona-meningkat-60-kasus|title=Data Terbaru: 369 Positif Corona, Meningkat 60 Kasus|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*Indonesia Minister of State-Owned Enterprises [[Erick Thohir]] that Indonesia has enough drugs for 60,000 COVID-19 patients, and by the end of March could supply up to 4.7 million face masks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4947190/erick-thohir-obat-pasien-corona-bisa-untuk-60-ribu-orang|title=Erick Thohir: Obat Pasien Corona Bisa untuk 60 Ribu Orang|last=Afriyadi|first=Achmad Dwi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*President Joko Widodo instructed his officials to shift budgetary priorities. Less prioritized budgets from the state budget (APBN) and regional budget (APBD) are to be reallocated to fund government efforts in combating the coronavirus pandemic, increasing the safety net for Indonesians, and to incentivize small and medium businesses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibizmedia.com/2020/03/20/hadapi-tantangan-pandemi-covid-19-ini-tiga-prioritas-kerja-pemerintah/|title=Hadapi Tantangan Pandemi Covid-19, Ini Tiga Prioritas Kerja Pemerintah|last=Sinambela|first=Maruli|date=2020-03-20|website=Vibizmedia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> He also promised to begin deploying rapid coronavirus testing, prioritizing South Jakarta as the worst-hit area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947166/pemerintah-mulai-rapid-test-corona-hari-ini-jakarta-jadi-prioritas|title=Pemerintah Mulai Rapid Test Corona Hari Ini, Jakarta Jadi Prioritas|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*Anies Baswedan declares a state of emergency in Jakarta for the next 14 days (2 April).<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947518/corona-ancam-jakarta-anies-tetapkan-status-tanggap-darurat-bencana|title=Corona Ancam Jakarta, Anies Tetapkan Status Tanggap Darurat Bencana|last=Wahid|first=Ahmad Bil|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> Anies also urged businesses to suspend operations, and he urged all stakeholders to take drastic actions to prevent the spread of the disease during the state of emergency.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4947558/anies-minta-perusahaan-hentikan-kegiatan-perkantoran|title=Anies Minta Perusahaan Hentikan Kegiatan Perkantoran|last=Wahid|first=Ahmad Bil|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/20/breaking-jakarta-declares-covid-19-emergency-urges-offices-to-suspend-operation-for-14-days.html|title=BREAKING: Jakarta declares COVID-19 emergency, urges offices to suspend operation for 14 days|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*After 9 positive cases of COVID-19, [[Khofifah Indar Parawansa]] declares a state of emergency for [[East Java]].<ref name=\"9Positive\">{{Cite web|url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/20/18240621/9-orang-positif-covid-19-khofifah-tetapkan-jatim-darurat-virus-corona|title=9 Orang Positif Covid-19, Khofifah Tetapkan Jatim Darurat Virus Corona|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-21|trans-title=9 Positive People Covid-19, Khofifah Determine Corona Virus Emergency East Java}}</ref>\n*Mayor of [[Bogor]], [[Bima Arya Sugiarto|Bima Arya]] has tested positive for COVID-19 after a trip to Turkey.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4946411/wali-kota-bogor-bima-arya-positif-corona|title=Wali Kota Bogor Bima Arya Positif Corona|last=Mawardi|first=Isal|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> Bima and all officials who went on the trip will comply with health protocols that include a minimum 14-day isolation at Bogor Senior Hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/20/bogor-mayor-one-other-official-test-positive-for-covid-19-after-trip-to-turkey.html|title=Bogor mayor, one other official test positive for COVID-19 after trip to Turkey|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*[[:id:Detri Warmanto|Detri Warmanto]] has tested positive for COVID-19. He is the son-in-law of the [[Ministry of Administrative and Bureaucratic Reform|Minister of Administrative and Bureaucratic Reform]], [[Tjahjo Kumolo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hot.detik.com/celeb/d-4947822/pemain-film-3-srikandi-detri-warmanto-positif-corona|title=Pemain Film '3 Srikandi', Detri Warmanto Positif Corona|last=Febrian|first=Prih Prawesti|website=detikhot|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*[[Istiqlal Mosque, Jakarta|Istiqlal mosque]] halted [[Friday prayer]] for 2 weeks after Anies Baswedan and [[Indonesian Council of Ulama]] requested to halt mass religious activities in Jakarta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liputan6.com/news/read/4206735/masjid-istiqlal-tiadakan-salat-jumat-selama-2-pekan|title=Masjid Istiqlal Tiadakan Salat Jumat Selama 2 Pekan|last=Liputan6.com|date=2020-03-20|website=liputan6.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n===21 March===\n*[[Indonesian Air Force]] is to fly its [[Lockheed C-130 Hercules|C-130 Hercules]] (A-1333) to the Chinese city of [[Shanghai]] on Saturday to pick up approximately 9 tonnes of medical equipment. The route is [[Malang]]-[[Natuna Regency|Natuna]]-Hainan-Shanghai. The equipment includes disposable masks, [[N95 mask]]s, protective clothing, goggles, gloves, shoe covers, infrared thermometers, and surgical caps.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4948247/tni-kerahkan-hercules-angkut-alat-kesehatan-corona-dari-shanghai|title=TNI Kerahkan Hercules Angkut Alat Kesehatan Corona dari Shanghai|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/20/covid-19-indonesian-military-to-get-medical-equipment-from-china.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesian military to get medical equipment from China|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n* One person died after having a fever and headaches. The victim, a Russian citizen, died in his boarding house on Jalan Bukit Tunggal Gang 5, West Denpasar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.balipost.com/news/2020/03/21/111174/Sempat-Demam,Warga-Rusia-Ditemukan...html|title=Sempat Demam, Warga Rusia Ditemukan Meninggal|last=POST|first=BALI|date=March 21, 2020|publisher=[[Bali Post Media Group]]|website=BALI POST PORTAL BERITA|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 81 new cases, totalling 450 cases of COVID-19 infection. Indonesia also announced 20 recovered and 38 deaths, an increase of 6 deaths since 20 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4948271/data-terbaru-kasus-positif-corona-jadi-450-bertambah-81|title=Data Terbaru: Kasus Positif Corona Jadi 450, Bertambah 81|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n===22 March===\n* [[:id:Ikatan Dokter Indonesia|Indonesia Medical Association]] (IDI) announced 6 doctors (Dr. Toni Daniel Silitonga; Dr. Ucok Martin; Dr. Djoko Judodjoko; Dr. Hadio Ali; Dr. Laurentius P; Dr. Adi Mirsaputra) have contracted COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4949139/6-dokter-indonesia-jadi-korban-pandemi-corona-ini-daftarnya|title=6 Dokter Indonesia Jadi Korban Pandemi Corona, Ini Daftarnya|last=Mahardhika|first=Anjar|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 64 new cases, a total of 514 cases.\n\n===23 March===\n* Indonesia announced 65 new cases, bringing the total to 579 cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4950124/per-23-maret-kasus-positif-corona-di-indonesia-jadi-579|title=Per 23 Maret, Kasus Positif Corona di Indonesia Jadi 579|last=Ibrahim|first=Gibran Maulana|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n*President Joko Widodo inaugurated the first COVID-19 makeshift hospital in the country at the [[Kemayoran Athletes Village|former athlete's village for the 2018 Asian Games]] in [[Kemayoran]], Jakarta. It was slated to be fitted with 3000 beds for patients requiring isolation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/23/09435921/presiden-jokowi-resmikan-rs-darurat-corona-di-wisma-atlet-kemayoran|title=Presiden Jokowi Resmikan RS Darurat Corona di Wisma Atlet Kemayoran|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4949291/dipermak-jadi-rs-hari-ini-wisma-atlet-siap-diisi-pasien-corona|title=Dipermak Jadi RS, Hari Ini Wisma Atlet Siap Diisi Pasien Corona|last=Hamdani|first=Trio|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> Later reports suggested that it would house only 1,800 beds for the first phase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/as-testing-expands-patients-at-indonesias-athletes-village-turn-hospital-expected-to|title=As coronavirus testing expands, cases at Indonesia's athlete's village-turned-hospital expected to rise dramatically|last=hermesauto|date=2020-03-25|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\n===24 March===\n* President Joko Widodo announced the cancellation of the annual national examination (''[[National Exam (Indonesia)|Ujian Nasional]]'') for all education levels, except Vocational High School (''Sekolah Menengah Kejuruan, SMK'') that has been done in almost half of all schools in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951217/jokowi-putuskan-tiadakan-un-2020-imbas-corona|title=Jokowi Putuskan Tiadakan UN 2020 Imbas Corona|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tirto.id/murid-smk-sudah-telanjur-un-nadiem-maaf-kalau-kalian-kecewa-eHlA|title=Murid SMK Sudah Tela