ex]]''\n*[[Maggie Gee (novelist)|Maggie Gee]] \u2013 ''[[The White Family]]''\n*[[Amin Maalouf]] \u2013 ''[[Balthasar's Odyssey]]'' (translated from French by [[Barbara Bray]])\n*[[Rohinton Mistry]] \u2013 ''[[Family Matters (novel)|Family Matters]]''\n*[[Atiq Rahimi]] \u2013 ''Earth and Ashes'' (translated from Persian by [[Erda\u011f G\u00f6knar]])\n*[[Olga Tokarczuk]] \u2013 ''House of Day, House of Night'' (translated from Polish by Antonia Lloyd-Jones)\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2005\n| align=center| &ndash;\n| {{sortname|Edward P. |Jones}}<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://global.unc.edu/pulitzer-prize-winner-to-read-speak-on-campus/ | title = Pulitzer Prize Winner to Read, Speak on Campus| publisher = UNC Global | accessdate = 23 June 2017}}</ref>\n|  English\n| ''[[The Known World]]''\n|\n* [[Diane Awerbuck]] \u2013 ''Gardening at Night''\n* [[Lars Saabye Christensen]] \u2013 ''The Half Brother'' (translated from Norwegian by Kenneth Steven)\n* [[Damon Galgut]] \u2013 ''The Good Doctor''\n* [[Douglas Glover (writer)|Douglas Glover]] \u2013 ''Elle''\n* [[Arnon Grunberg]] \u2013 ''Phantom Pain'' (translated from Dutch by Sam Garrett)\n* [[Shirley Hazzard]] \u2013 ''[[The Great Fire (Hazzard novel)|The Great Fire]]''\n* [[Christoph Hein]] \u2013 ''Willenbrock'' (translated from German by [[Philip Boehm]])\n* [[Frances Itani]] \u2013 ''[[Deafening (novel)|Deafening]]''\n* [[Jonathan Lethem]] \u2013 ''[[The Fortress of Solitude (novel)|The Fortress of Solitude]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2006\n| [[File:Colm toibin 2006.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sortname|Colm|T\u00f3ib\u00edn}}<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2009/05/03/magazine/03toibin-t.html | work = The New York Times | title = His Irish Diaspora | first = Alex | last = Witchel | date = 3 May 2009 | accessdate = 23 June 2017 | url-status = live | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160716183822/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/05/03/magazine/03toibin-t.html | archivedate = 16 July 2016 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n| En