Lean]])\n* [[Yasmine Gooneratne]] \u2013 ''The Sweet & Simple Kind''\n* [[Gail Jones]] \u2013 ''[[Dreams of Speaking]]''\n* [[Sayed Kashua]] \u2013 ''Let It Be Morning'' (translated from Hebrew by Miriam Shlesinger)\n* [[Yasmina Khadra]] \u2013 ''[[The Attack (novel)|The Attack]]'' (translated from French by John Cullen)\n* [[Patrick McCabe (novelist)|Patrick McCabe]] \u2013 ''Winterwood''\n* [[Andre\u00ef Makine]] \u2013 ''The Woman Who Waited'' (translated from French by [[Geoffrey Strachan]])\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2009\n| align=center| &ndash;\n| {{sortname|Michael|Thomas|Michael Thomas (author)}}<ref name=w2009/>\n| English\n| ''[[Man Gone Down]]'' {{double dagger}}\n|\n* [[Junot D\u00edaz]] \u2013 ''[[The Brief Wondrous Life of Oscar Wao]]''\n* [[Jean Echenoz]] \u2013 ''Ravel'' (translated from French by [[Linda Coverdale]])\n* [[Mohsin Hamid]] \u2013 ''[[The Reluctant Fundamentalist]]''\n* [[Travis Holland]] \u2013 ''[[The Archivist's Story]]''\n* [[Roy Jacobsen]] \u2013 ''The Burnt-Out Town of Miracles'' (translated from Norwegian by Don Shaw and [[Don Bartlett]])\n* [[David Leavitt]] \u2013 ''[[The Indian Clerk]]''\n* [[Indra Sinha]] \u2013 ''[[Animal's People]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2010\n| [[File:Gerbrand Bakker.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sortname|Gerbrand|Bakker|Gerbrand Bakker (novelist)}}<ref>{{Cite web| url = https://www.theguardian.com/books/2010/jun/17/gerbrand-bakker-impac-prize| title = Dutch gardener reaps Impac prize| first = Alison| last = Flood| work = The Guardian| accessdate = 23 June 2017| date = 17 June 2010| url-status = live| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100619091020/http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2010/jun/17/gerbrand-bakker-impac-prize| archivedate = 19 June 2010| df = dmy-all}}</ref>\n| Dutch\n| ''[[The Twin (novel)|The Twin]]''<br />(translated by [[David Colmer]])\n|\n* [[Muriel Barbery]] \u2013 ''[[The Elegance of the Hedgehog]]'' (translated from French by Alison Anderson)\n* [[Robert Edric]] \u2013 ''In Zodiac Light''\n* [[Christoph Hein]] \u2013 ''Settlement'' (translated from German by Philip Boehm)\n* [[Zo\u00eb Heller]] \u2013 ''[[The Believers (novel)|The Believers]]''\n* [[Joseph O'Neill (writer, born 1964)|Joseph O'Neill]] \u2013 ''[[Netherland (novel)|Netherland]]''\n* [[Ross Raisin]] \u2013 ''God's Own Country''\n* [[Marilynne Robinson]] \u2013 ''[[Home (Robinson novel)|Home]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2011\n| [[File:Colum McCann Portrait.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sortname|Colum|McCann}}<ref>{{cite news|first=Charlie|last=Taylor|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2011/0615/breaking34.html|title=Colum McCann wins Impac award|work=The Irish Times|date=15 June 2011|accessdate=15 June 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111224004314/http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/breaking/2011/0615/breaking34.html|archivedate=24 December 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| English\n| ''[[Let the Great World Spin]]''\n|\n*[[Michael Crummey]] \u2013 ''Galore''\n*[[Barbara Kingsolver]] \u2013 ''[[The Lacuna]]''\n*[[Yiyun Li]] \u2013 ''The Vagrants''\n*[[David Malouf]] \u2013 ''[[Ransom (Malouf novel)|Ransom]]''\n*[[Joyce Carol Oates]] \u2013 ''[[Little Bird of Heaven]]''\n*[[Craig Silvey]] \u2013 ''[[Jasper Jones]]''\n*[[Colm T\u00f3ib\u00edn]] \u2013 ''[[Brooklyn (novel)|Brooklyn]]''\n*[[William Trevor]] \u2013 ''[[Love and Summer]]''\n*[[Evie Wyld]] \u2013 ''[[After the Fire, A Still Small Voice]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2012\n| align=center| &ndash;\n| {{sortname|Jon|McGregor}}<ref>{{cite news|first=Alison|last=Flood|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2012/jun/13/jon-mcgregor-wins-impac-literary-award|title=Jon McGregor wins International Impac Dublin Literary Award|work=The Guardian|date=13 June 2012|accessdate=13 June 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306153718/http://www.theguardian.com/books/2012/jun/13/jon-mcgregor-wins-impac-literary-award|archivedate=6 March 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| English\n| ''[[Even the Dogs]]''\n|\n*[[Jon Bauer (